// Description ::
// The following guide has been designed to help the user install Processing on a Raspberry Pi!

// Backgorund ::
// What is processing?
// Processing is an open-source development environment for several computer languages (including Java, C++, Android, and Python).
// Processing can be used to develop applications for micro-controllers such as Arduinos!

// Guide ::

1.0- Always update and upgrade raspbian

> sudo apt-get update
> sudo apt-get upgrade

2.0- Download Processing for Raspberry Pi

> curl https://processing.org/download/install-arm.sh | sudo sh

// Follow download instructions if any...

// References ::

> https://www.raspberrypi.org/blog/now-available-for-download-processing/